<dl id="n36198b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36198b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36198b"> 198(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ halter</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Anxious to preserve the judicial code of the State from the additions and amendments of country members and seekers of popularity, <font color="green">[Charondas the Locrian legislator]</font> ordained that, whoever <mark>proposed a new law should do it with a halter about his neck</mark>; whereby, in case his proposition were rejected, they should just hang him up&mdash;and there the matter ended. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 162</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
